s first job as a pharmacy delivery boy to his graduation from the University of Montreal's Faculty of Pharmacy - when he had already started his own pharmaceutical company - through the crucial moments that created an international business, Goodman depicts stirring accounts of Montreal's Jewish community and the development of the global pharmaceutical industry. Along the way, he presents vivid, generous portraits of colleagues and business collaborators. To Make a Difference is a powerful rags-to-riches story but it is also much more - it is a heartfelt, candid, and inspiring exploration of what makes our lives rich, what we value, and why.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aBusinesspeople -- Québec (Province) -- Montréal -- Biography. 0aBusinesspeoplezQuébec (Province)zMontréalvBiography. 0aBusinesspeoplezQuébec (Province). 0aJews -- Québec (Province) -- Montréal -- Biography. 0aJewszQuébec (Province)zMontréalvBiography. 0aJewszQuébec (Province). 0aPharmaceutical industryzQuébec (Province)zMontréalxHistory. 0aPharmaceutical industryzQuébec (Province). 0aPharmacists -- Québec (Province) -- Montréal -- Biography. 0aPharmacistszQuébec (Province)zMontréalvBiography. 0aPharmacistszQuébec (Province). 0aPhilanthropists -- Québec (Province) -- Montréal -- Biography. 0aPhilanthropistszQuébec (Province)zMontréalvBiography. 0aPhilanthropistszQuébec (Province). 0aSuccess in businesszQuébec (Province)zMontréalvBiography. 0aSuccess in businesszQuébec (Province). 0aSuccesszQuébec (Province)zMontréalvBiography. 0aSuccesszQuébec (Province). 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Business.2bisacsh1 aYanofsky, Joel, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2014z978311127407208iTitle is 